entry.title: Flood Warning issued May 20 at 8:17AM CDT until May 20 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Omaha/Valley NE
entry.summary:

Heavy rain, over a large area, has fallen in Saunders County, specifically around Prague and north of Malmo. * WHEN...Until 500 PM CDT Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 817 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Flooding is already occurring in the warned area. Between 2 and 4 inches of rain have fallen. - Flooding impacts will continue, but no additional rainfall is expected. - For Wahoo Creek at Wahoo: At 12:15am the stage was 18.74 feet. entry.summary: Snowfall will move across the Dalton Highway Corridor through the Brooks Range to Deadhorse and the Arctic Ocean this evening through Tuesday evening. Accumulations of 3 to 7 inches are expected along the Dalton Highway south of Deadhorse to the Brooks Range. Snow accumulations generally increase closer to the Brooks Range. Roads may become slick and travelers should expect potential travel delays.
